Watch This


Changes:
 - Disable menu items & buttons (OR show messages if it's REALLY helpful)

Misc
 - WPF: Make files double-clickable (associate with WatchThis.app/exe)
 - Connect Ctrl+Tab & Shift+Ctrl+Tab
 - Hide / Disable List window while slideshow active

Global settings
 - Slideshows directory: <Pictures>/WatchThisSlideshows
 - Default background color: black
 - Default slide duration: 10 seconds
 - ListView font & size
 - Length of time controls are visible: 2 seconds

Edit tab
 - Properties button => Properties dialog
 - Replace Name with Description

Saved tab
 - implement Edit button (load to Edit tab)

Properties dialog
 - Per slideshow
 - Background color
 - Manual versus automatic
 - Fullscreen or not


Slideshow
 - + / - to increase / decrease slide duration
 - Check keyboard shortcuts (q, f, left arrow, right arrow, space, +, -)
 - Info display: timestamp (various forms), directory name (various forms), file name, ...

WPF
 - Transitions


Features
  Multiscreen
  	- One slideshow, one or all screens
  	- Keyboard controls 'active' screen/window
  	- Visible controls per window; they control the window they're on

  Multiple slideshows
  	- Run more than one slideshow at a time
  	- Scenario: Two different slideshows, one for each screen
  	- Same keyboard/controls interaction as Multiscreen

  Info banner
	 - This text banner shows one or more of:
	 	- timestamp: YYYY/MM/DD, ...
	 	- directory name: parent, +grand-parent, +great-grand-parent, ...
	 	- filename
	 	- EXIF/XXX tags
	 - Font & size are configurable
	 - Opacity/transparency
	 - Global settings
	 	- Default fields
	 	- Default font/size
	 - Slideshow settings
	 	- Show or hide
	 	- fields
	 	- font/size
	 - Slideshow
	 	- Show or hide
	 	- Keyboard shortcut: i

